# Sentinel agent workflow

- Do not add long-lived throwaway helpers (e.g. one-off Python patch scripts). Prefer in-place edits. If a temporary script is unavoidable, delete it before ending the task.
- Keep existing project scripts under `agent/tools/` and similar unless the user asks to change them.
- After finishing work that modifies the agent (Rust, Tauri, or `agent/ui-src`), run a release MSI build from `agent/`:

  `cargo tauri build`

  Artifact (x64): `agent/target/x86_64-pc-windows-msvc/release/bundle/msi/Sentinel Agent_<version>_x64_en-US.msi`

- If the CLI exits with a signing error about `TAURI_SIGNING_PRIVATE_KEY`, the MSI may still be produced; check the `bundle/msi` directory. Signing is optional for local installs.
